Lyrics:
The sun is pounding through the window
Don’t know where I’ve been, though
Withering, I turn from below
What should I force myself to do now?
Losing all my spirit, I hide my face and fall to the ground

The pavement burns in hazy visions
Singing ever with it, soli, cicadas begin
My mind is muddied up and melting
Filled up to bursting, saturated puddles to mist

My isolation starts constricting me
In a mess I stumble, gritting my teeth

God, I’m melting, melting
Take away the trembling
Come and lend a hand and borrow some heat
While I’m melting, melting
Leaving the scene, far before me
You vanished like sparks within the breeze
And I’m melting, melting
Like a fading melody, like a summer chime when the winds find a peace
Cause nothing, nothing
Matters to me, let it repeat
The feelings will fade within the heat
Right?
